# HackViolet 2024
 - February 3-4, 2024
 - Association for Women in Computing at Virginia Tech University 
 - Blacksburg, Virginia, United States

## Event Summary

Our hackathon is unique because it is a female-empowerment hackathon and through our event we strive to empower underrepresented minorities in the technology field. A few of our most interesting workshops and events were mentor speed dating, LeetCode competition, and technical interview workshops. GitHub was featured at our event as a required part of all project submissions and we encouraged hackers to practice using Git. To prepare our hackers, we held an Command Line and Git, and a GitHub CoPilot workshop. We utilized Git to teach and encourage our hackers to practice version control and learn collaborative coding practices.

