## Impact of GitHub Grant
We used the GitHub Grant funds to fund some of our workshops and activties that took place during HackViolet. We also used funds to support our mentorship program this year. This year we saw a large increase in mentorship interest. We provided refreshments and supplies to our mentors and mentees so that they could have a more enjoyable mentorship experience. These funds helped us support our hackers who were looking for mentors during the weekend. We used the funding to support our mentors during their shifts which in turn allowed them to better help our hackers. Additionally, we used a portion of funding to provide extra/emergency refreshments, such as snacks and drinks, throughout the weekend to our hackers and mentors.

## Top Projects

Our Best Overall Winners are:
- 1st Place: Walk 4 Water https://devpost.com/software/walk-4-water
- 2nd Place: SafeSound https://devpost.com/software/safesound-4atsrn

Our Best Hack to Support Winners are: 
- 1st Place: Baby Blues https://devpost.com/software/baby-blues
- 2nd Place: https://devpost.com/software/shenetworks-25fzi9

We had many more amazing projects in addition to these, such as a project that used a projector to display clothes on a live model and a hardware/robotic project.

Overall, our hackers used GitHubt to collaboratively program and share their project/source code with our judging team. 

